  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 325 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Season the pork ribs with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium‑high heat and sear the ribs on all sides until browned.",
    "Remove the ribs and add the diced onion, minced garlic, and bell pepper, cooking until softened.",
    "Pour in the beef broth and crushed tomatoes, then stir in the dried thyme.",
    "Return the ribs to the pot, cover it, and transfer it to the oven to bake for 150 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven, stir the stew, squeeze in fresh lemon juice, and sprinkle with chopped parsley.",
    "Serve the stew hot over a side of cooked maize or millet."
